    <stitle>PROPELLER SHAFT - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid personal injury always set parking brake (air brake equipped vehicles) and block
                        wheels to prevent vehicle from moving.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
            <title>FULL ROUND END YOKES</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block the wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark the slip joint with a marking stick or paint to assure proper alignment upon
                    reassembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place jack stands under propeller shaft to support it during removal.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Carefully bend tabs of the locking straps (if equipped) away from the bolt heads with a
                    chisel (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0600110">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0600110" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0600110" filename="../figg06/G0600110.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 10. Bend Tabs of Locking Straps Away From Bolt Heads</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four bolts from the two bearing assemblies connected to the transmission or
                    axle end yoke (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0600111">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0600111" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0600111" filename="../figg06/G0600111.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 11. Remove Bolts From Bearing Assemblies Connected to Transmission or Axle End
                        Yoke
                    </caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the bearing assemblies from the yoke using a universal joint service tool.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Free the cross from the end yoke by tilting it while collapsing the propeller shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0600112">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0600112" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0600112" filename="../figg06/G0600112.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px" scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                    <caption>Figure 12. Free Cross From End Yoke</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
